  "response": "The United States generally has limited internet censorship compared to some other countries. The First Amendment protects freedom of speech online, and there are few broad restrictions. However, some specific content can be legally restricted, such as:\n\n1. Child pornography\n2. Explicit copyright infringement\n3. Direct incitement to violence\n4. Specific types of harassment\n5. Certain national security-related content\n\nPlatforms like social media sites can also moderate content according to their own policies. But overall, the U.S. internet remains relatively open compared to countries with more extensive censorship.",
